{"schema": {"fields":[{"type":"integer","name":"index"},{"type":"string","name":"author_association"},{"type":"string","name":"body"},{"type":"datetime","name":"created_at"},{"type":"string","name":"html_url"},{"type":"integer","name":"id"},{"type":"string","name":"issue_url"},{"type":"string","name":"node_id"},{"type":"datetime","name":"updated_at"},{"type":"string","name":"url"},{"type":"string","name":"user"}],"pandas_version":"0.20.0","primaryKey":["index"]}, "data": [{"index":0,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"Hi @kswope \n\nHere is a working jsbin:\nhttp:\/\/jsbin.com\/iWiCInO\/14\/edit?html,js,output\n\nYour issue is related to the recent issue #4874 \n\n@mrdoob and @WestLangley ,\nThis is more evidence that something should be changed with the THREE.OrthographicCamera constructor arguments for near\/far planes.  kswope was thinking like I was before WestLangley pointed out the right way to set up the ortho camera.\n\nIf you can't make the constructor more strict (without breaking or changing three.js examples), maybe a paragraph can be added under this constructor inside the documentation detailing the correct way to think about and use the ortho camera.\n","created_at":"2014-06-04T05:36:09.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4880#issuecomment-45053159","id":45053159,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4880","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ1MDUzMTU5","updated_at":"2014-06-04T05:39:37.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/45053159","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/3434843?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/erichlof","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM0MzQ4NDM=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"erichlof","type":"User","id":3434843,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/orgs"}},{"index":1,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"@kswope \n\nAll you need to do is position your camera so it can see your entire scene.\n\n```\ncamera = new THREE.OrthographicCamera(\n    window.innerWidth \/ -2, \/\/ frustum left plane\n    window.innerWidth \/ 2, \/\/ frustum right plane.\n    window.innerHeight \/ 2, \/\/ frustum top plane.\n    window.innerHeight \/ -2, \/\/ frustum bottom plane. \n    1, \/\/ frustum near plane.\n    100 \/\/ frustum far plane.\n);\ncamera.position.z = 10;\n```\n\n@erichlof \n\n`near` and `far` planes are specified for `OrthographicCamera` exactly the same way they are specified for `PerspectiveCamera`.\n","created_at":"2014-06-04T14:19:21.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4880#issuecomment-45096180","id":45096180,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4880","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ1MDk2MTgw","updated_at":"2014-06-04T14:19:21.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/45096180","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":2,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"@WestLangley \nOk but should negative values be allowed in the constructor?  Either way you and @mrdoob want to go with this, I might do a minor PR to the ortho camera docs going into more detail with the example code snippet comments as well as a short paragraph below the snippet as to what's going on. Then we can direct ortho camera issues there instead of the three.js general issue tracker.  Sound good to you? \n","created_at":"2014-06-04T16:21:53.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4880#issuecomment-45112942","id":45112942,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4880","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ1MTEyOTQy","updated_at":"2014-06-04T16:21:53.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/45112942","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/3434843?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/erichlof","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM0MzQ4NDM=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"erichlof","type":"User","id":3434843,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/orgs"}},{"index":3,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"@erichlof \n\n> Ok but should negative values be allowed in the constructor?\n\nthree.js does not typically test for the validity of parameter values. (Whether it should is a separate issue). Also, in this case, a negative near plane causes no harm, so I would be inclined not to restrict the user.\n\nThe real problem is that some users do not understand what they are doing. If you would like to improve the docs, I am all in favor of that.\n","created_at":"2014-06-04T18:04:11.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4880#issuecomment-45127171","id":45127171,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4880","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ1MTI3MTcx","updated_at":"2014-06-04T18:04:11.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/45127171","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":4,"author_association":"NONE","body":"Because I haven't positioned the camera did I trick myself by looking out from the origin backwards from what I expected and I corrected for this by flipping the near and far planes?\n","created_at":"2014-06-04T18:04:32.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4880#issuecomment-45127219","id":45127219,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4880","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ1MTI3MjE5","updated_at":"2014-06-04T18:04:32.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/45127219","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/kswope\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/kswope\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/321586?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/kswope","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/kswope\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/kswope","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/kswope\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMyMTU4Ng==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/kswope\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/kswope\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/kswope\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"kswope","type":"User","id":321586,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/kswope\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/kswope\/orgs"}},{"index":5,"author_association":"NONE","body":"Ok I got it, those last two parameters, near and far are the positive relative distance from the camera, not absolute positions in space or something else.  I found this info only in a book. Even though its probably obvious to the experienced I'm sure there are legions of noobs using this library.\n\nWhy not change the docs from\n\n```\nnear \u2014 Camera frustum near plane.\nfar \u2014 Camera frustum far plane.\n```\n\nto something like \n\n```\nnear \u2014 Camera frustum near plane (distance from camera)\nfar \u2014 Camera frustum far plane (distance from camera).\n```\n\nThe book I'm reading defines near very clearly as \"The near property defines from how close to the camera the Three.js library should render the scene. Normally we set this to a very small value to directly render everything from the position of the camera.\"\n","created_at":"2014-06-05T01:17:54.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4880#issuecomment-45171407","id":45171407,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4880","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ1MTcxNDA3","updated_at":"2014-06-05T01:17:54.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/45171407","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/kswope\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/kswope\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/321586?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/kswope","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/kswope\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/kswope","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/kswope\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMyMTU4Ng==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/kswope\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/kswope\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/kswope\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"logi