agree - I usually find that a setting of '1' for the near plane of a perspective camera gives me objects close enough to the camera not to pop out of view too soon when approaching the objects.  But also like WestLangley said, the number is big enough to allow precision towards the far part of the frustum, and you get correct z-buffer results (where nearer objects must overlap slightly farther objects).\n","created_at":"2014-06-05T02:07:21.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4880#issuecomment-45173854","id":45173854,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4880","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ1MTczODU0","updated_at":"2014-06-05T02:07:21.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/45173854","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/3434843?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/erichlof","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM0MzQ4NDM=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"erichlof","type":"User","id":3434843,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/orgs"}},{"index":8,"author_association":"NONE","body":"Thats fine, but I was more pointing out the part \"The near property defines from how close to the camera the Three.js library should render the scene\", which is much more informative than \"Camera frustum near plane\"\n","created_at":"2014-06-05T03:37:24.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4880#issuecomment-45177913","id":45177913,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4880","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ1MTc3OTEz","updated_at":"2014-06-05T03:37:24.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/45177913","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/kswope\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/kswope\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/321586?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/kswope","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/kswope\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/kswope","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/kswope\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMyMTU4Ng==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/kswope\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/kswope\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/kswope\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"kswope","type":"User","id":321586,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/kswope\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/kswope\/orgs"}},{"index":9,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"The `near` (`far`) property specifies the distance from the camera to the near (far) clipping plane of the frustum.\n","created_at":"2014-06-05T03:58:53.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4880#issuecomment-45178753","id":45178753,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4880","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ1MTc4NzUz","updated_at":"2014-06-05T03:58:53.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/45178753","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.c